<subSubSection pageId="14" pageNumber="18" type="discussion">
<paragraph pageId="14" pageNumber="18" type="mainText">
<pageBreakToken pageId="14" pageNumber="18" start="start">Variation</pageBreakToken>
. In Europe and North America the 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Amaranthaceae" genus="Chenopodium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="14" pageNumber="18" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="hybridum">C. hybridum</taxonomicName>
aggregate comprises two well-delimited taxa, viz. 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Amaranthaceae" genus="Chenopodium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="14" pageNumber="18" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="hybridum">C. hybridum</taxonomicName>
in Europe and 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Amaranthaceae" genus="Chenopodium" genus.bestMatchDistance="44388" genus.bestMatchVote="2" genus.innerRound="1" genus.outerRound="1" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="14" pageNumber="18" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="simplex">C. simplex</taxonomicName>
(see rare casuals) in North America. In Asia it is represented by several taxa. A specimen from S Upl Sollentuna (Rotebro) 1925 belongs to one of these, having large leaf-blades and large seeds with coarsely rugulose but not pitted seed-coat.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="14" pageNumber="18" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageId="14" pageNumber="18" type="mainText">
Similar taxa. 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Amaranthaceae" genus="Chenopodium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="14" pageNumber="18" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="hybridum">Chenopodium hybridum</taxonomicName>
is vegetatively 
<normalizedToken originalValue="±" pageId="14" pageNumber="18">+/-</normalizedToken>
indistinguishable from the North American 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Amaranthaceae" genus="Chenopodium" genus.bestMatchDistance="44190" genus.bestMatchVote="2" genus.innerRound="1" genus.outerRound="1" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="14" pageNumber="18" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="simplex">C. simplex</taxonomicName>
(rare casual), but clearly different in seed characters.
</paragraph>
